# Project Rules and Guidelines

## Language and Documentation
- All code outputs, comments, and documentation must be in English
- Variable names, function names, and other code identifiers must be in English
- Commit messages must be in English

## Project Structure and Development
- All development must strictly follow README.md and PLAN.md guidelines
- No arbitrary project changes without updating PLAN.md first
- Any significant changes must be documented in both README.md and PLAN.md

## Additional Guidelines
- Follow consistent code formatting and style
- Document all major functions and components
- Keep the codebase clean and maintainable
- Regular commits with meaningful commit messages
- Test coverage for critical functionality
- Security best practices must be followed
- Performance optimization considerations
